    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>You flip open the cover of the Tome of Singing Thorns. On the title page is a castoff's tattoo divided into five curving, triangular shapes the color of each Tide, with a small inscription beneath. You try turning to the next page, but can't - it's as if the pages are a solid block of paper. 

You lay your hand on the title page's rough, somewhat metallic surface, and the sharp triangular shapes spring up around your fingers with a vibrating hum. 

{SOUND: Each thorn mentioned in this conversation plays a unique note. The puzzle is solved by playing them in ascending order. This melody was a lullaby sung by TCG to his daughter before he became the utter jerkwad we know. Each time the player plays a right note, it sustains, joining the others. When they screw up, the notes fade out, and the player starts over. Let me know if you have any questions, or if you don't have the time to come up with a song. I can throw something together if that's the case.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
