    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>The notes surrounding you scatter into silence, as if swept aside by an impatient hand. The book blurs open, flipping from page to page faster than you can read. 

But still, you catch glimpses - neat tables of strange creatures and their Tidal affinities. Dwindling question marks on each page as the author understood more and more. 

And through it all, you feel the book reading *you*. Touching parts of your mind, erasing uncertainties, and reopening portions that have long been closed.  
{SOUND: The notes repeat in order, then scatter with a sound like a bunch of guitar strings breaking at once.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>67</ID>
      <DefaultText>You finish the song again. This time, the music doesn't fade. The book twists in your hands, and begins flipping from the end of the book backwards.

You see, in inky shadows, a bed, and the dying young woman upon it. She clutches the blankets to her throat, fists shaking. Silent tears wet the pillow beneath her cheeks. Her teeth are set against the pain. 

And the singing continues, cracked with the hope that it will bring her peace and let her sleep.  
{SOUND: Female voice humming the lullaby. Fades when the Player leaves this node.}</DefaultText>
